{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"PHASE 1 investigation progress (dossier):\n\nSYMPTOM (CI run 29619412488, job 88011317607, built commit 95cbc7bb4): verify-identity gate exit 1; summary '602 verified, 4958 unsigned, 0 unknown-author, 0 bad-signature, 206 key-not-valid-at-era (5766 in scope)'. Enforced (non-grandfathered) failures = key_not_valid_at_era on compacted (ledger) entries across creation-channel epic tickets (jira-reb-977, e622, 568c, 6fe2, ...) + ~6 unsigned rec-0000 COMPLETION_VERDICT live sidecars.\n\nKEY MECHANISM (verify_authorship.py): a compacted ledger entry carries commit_sha; the SNAPSHOT for jira-reb-977 records ALL 31 ledger entries with commit_sha=null. The gate re-resolves null via resolve_position_commit (git log --diff-filter=A -- *POSITION*.json). If that returns None, _is_enforced(None) FAIL-CLOSES to ENFORCED and the era check at commit=None yields key_not_valid_at_era. So the entire failure reduces to: resolve returned None in CI.\n\nREPRODUCTION FINDINGS:\n- STALE global rebar v0.8.0 (LACKS the 4cc3ffbbb fixes: no sidecar-drop, no ledger null re-resolution) run over the CURRENT full store reproduces CI EXACTLY: 4958 unsigned + 206 key-not-valid-at-era.\n- FIXED 95cbc7bb4 build (per-ticket) classifies those same jira-reb-977/e622/568c/6fe2 ledger entries as VERIFIED + grandfathered (0 enforced) because resolve_position_commit finds the real pre-anchor add commit (e.g. 095b931e, 2026-07-16).\n- Shallow-history hypothesis REJECTED (full tickets fetch into a shallow code repo still yields full tickets history).\n\nOPEN QUESTION (running now): does the FIXED 95cbc7bb4 build clear the 206 at WHOLE-STORE scale? If yes -> CI's stale-matching numbers mean CI effectively ran without the fixes' effect (env/build issue), i.e. the 'fixes landed' precondition was not actually satisfied in the CI build. If the fixed build ALSO yields 206 -> the 4cc3ffbbb re-resolution does not hold whole-store. Two independent code investigators running in parallel."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784336553644074001,"uuid":"b0cda26d-38a9-4a77-9318-4c21e8df01ae"}